BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:wzsRINJvR8BkwZAPEUj4X
SUMMARY:Surge Reproductive Justice Presents: The Ebony Canal
DTSTAMP:20260331T230133Z
DTSTART:20260411T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Black Maternal Health Week with My Time for Massage a
	nd Surge Reproductive Justice. Join us for a powerful community screening 
	of The Ebony Canal. This documentary explores the history and current stat
	e of Black maternal health while illuminating the path toward healing and 
	justice. This is a free event centering Black mothers\, birthing people\, 
	and families. Together we will center our joy and resilience. This is a ca
	ll to action for community to come together to support Black mothers and o
	ur babies. Enjoy a community resource fair\, local vendors\, food\, and fr
	ee childcare! Also\, free wellness and prenatal bags for the first 30 expe
	cting parents who register. Register Here\n\nhttps://rainierartscenter.org
	/events/surge-reproductive-justice-presents-the-ebony-canal/
URL:https://rainierartscenter.org/events/surge-reproductive-justice-present
	s-the-ebony-canal/
LOCATION:Whole Building\, Rainier Arts Center\, 3515 S Alaska St\, Seattle\
	, WA 98118
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
